[
    {
        "content": "<p>How come the spec dictates that the operation sign '$' must be preceded with a '/' ? Is it a coincidence  - as handling the searchparam '?' is allowed with and without a preceding '/'</p>",
        "id": 153923326,
        "sender_full_name": "Jens Villadsen",
        "timestamp": 1512643159
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>umm, ? should not be preceded by a /</p>",
        "id": 153923332,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1512643888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>right - ? is not preceded by a / - so why is $ stated to do so. I was just wondering</p>",
        "id": 153923390,
        "sender_full_name": "Jens Villadsen",
        "timestamp": 1512662293
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>? is considered options to a request to the type manager to list all the resources of the type</p>",
